C/ Exercises PREP_LITERAL / MAKE_FIXED_LIT / ROUND_SCALAR — the AW-with-
C/ FIXER path that turns a scalar literal into an integer.  Verifies the
C/ ADR/SDR/CD chain that follows AW (integer detection / range check)
C/ still works after the ibm_dp_addsub guard-digit refactor.

 PREP_LITERAL: PROGRAM;
    DECLARE I1 INTEGER INITIAL(3);
    DECLARE I2 INTEGER INITIAL(3.0);
    DECLARE I3 INTEGER INITIAL(3.4);
    DECLARE I4 INTEGER INITIAL(-7);
    DECLARE I5 INTEGER INITIAL(-7.6);
    DECLARE I6 INTEGER INITIAL(0);
    WRITE(6) I1, I2, I3, I4, I5, I6;
Y %SVCI(0);
 CLOSE PREP_LITERAL;
